{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-0114"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Sugar-Cane Plantation Operations Coordination"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "0114"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :agriculture/sugar-cane-growing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:food-security :rural-employment :environmental-stewardship]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :cane-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :audit-ledger]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies [:telemetry :optimization :dmn :bpmn]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "CaneOpsAdvisor ⊣ Cane Operations Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph
 (langgraph.graph, caneops.operation/build), append-only audit ledger
 (caneops.store/ledger + append-ledger!, MemStore and a DatomicStore
 backed by langchain.db via langchain-store.core). A back-office
 OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor for sugar-cane plantation management
 (perennial crop, ratoon-cropping cycles) -- not direct field-equipment
 operation authority and not pre-harvest-burn or pesticide-application-
 decision authority. Four ops (`:log-field-record` /
 `:schedule-field-operation` / `:flag-crop-health-concern` /
 `:order-supplies`), all `:effect :propose` only. Six HARD invariants
 (field-not-registered, no-execution, equipment-or-decision-blocked,
 op-not-allowed, field-record-invalid, ratoon-cycle-invalid) elaborate
 this blueprint's Governor. Crop-health-concern flagging ALWAYS
 escalates to a human grower/agronomist via the compiled graph's
 `:request-approval` node (`interrupt-before`, checkpoint-based
 resume); `:log-field-record` and `:schedule-field-operation` are the
 ops eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when the Governor is
 clean. Every commit/hold/approval-rejected decision lands in the
 append-only ledger -- 37 tests / 116 assertions green
 (`clojure -M:dev:test`), demo runnable end-to-end against both Store
 backends (`clojure -M:dev:run`)."}
